<body>
  <h1>EmulatorJS Controls Manual</h1>
  <p>
    This guide explains the default keyboard controls for Game Boy Advance (GBA), 
    Super Nintendo (SNES), and Game Boy Color (GBC) when using EmulatorJS. 
    HTML5-based games may have their own control schemes, which can differ from these defaults.
  </p>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Pokemon and Zelda</h2>
    <ul class="keys">
      <li><b>A:</b> <code>Z</code></li>
      <li><b>B:</b> <code>X</code></li>
      <li><b>L:</b> <code>Q</code></li>
      <li><b>R:</b> <code>E</code></li>
      <li><b>Start:</b> <code>Enter</code></li>
      <li><b>Select:</b> <code>V</code></li>
      <li><b>D-Pad:</b> Arrow Keys</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Top Gear and NBA Jam</h2>
    <ul class="keys">
      <li><b>A:</b> <code>Z</code></li>
      <li><b>B:</b> <code>X</code></li>
      <li><b>X:</b> <code>A</code></li>
      <li><b>Y:</b> <code>S</code></li>
      <li><b>L:</b> <code>Q</code></li>
      <li><b>R:</b> <code>E</code></li>
      <li><b>Start:</b> <code>Enter</code></li>
      <li><b>Select:</b> <code>V</code></li>
      <li><b>D-Pad:</b> Arrow Keys</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Tetris</h2>
    <ul class="keys">
      <li><b>A:</b> <code>Z</code></li>
      <li><b>B:</b> <code>X</code></li>
      <li><b>Start:</b> <code>Enter</code></li>
      <li><b>Select:</b> <code>V</code></li>
      <li><b>D-Pad:</b> Arrow Keys</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Slope and Minecraft</h2>
    <p>
      HTML5-based games can use any control setup defined by the developer. 
      Unlike console emulators, there is no universal standard. 
      Always check the gameâ€™s instructions, as keys may differ or allow customization.
    </p>
  </div>

  <footer>
    Note: You can usually remap these keys in the EmulatorJS configuration if needed.
  </footer>
